Anthropic ships scheduled Claude agents with secret API key vaults and para=
llel subagents
3,760 Likes
Claude agents used to die when you closed the tab. That changes now with th=
ree new features.
Here is what shipped:
Scheduled deployments (public beta):
Give an agent a cron schedule, and each time it fires, the agent starts a n=
ew session and completes its task with no scheduler for you to build or hos=
t. Perfect for nightly data syncs, weekly compliance scans, or daily digest=
s.
Environment variables in vaults (public beta):
The agent never sees your real API key. The sandbox holds only a placeholde=
r, and the real key is attached at the network boundary, only on requests t=
o domains you allow.
Dynamic workflows in Claude Code (now GA):
Claude writes its own orchestration program on the fly, then runs it across=
 many separate agents, each with a clean context window and one focused job=
.
One team deleted all the scheduling infrastructure they had built in-house =
and replaced it with scheduled deployments, simplifying their stack. That i=
s the kind of boilerplate this kills.
READ MORE
