<div style=3D"margin-top:0;">
<p><b>Claude Fable 5</b> just landed in Cursor, and the numbers are hard to=
 ignore. It hit <b>72.9% on CursorBench</b>, a test built from real, messy,=
 multi-file coding tasks pulled from actual Cursor sessions. That's 8 point=
s above the previous best.</p><p>So what makes it different? It's built to =
stay focused across very long tasks without losing track of what you asked =
it to do. It holds intent across long sessions and drives tasks to completi=
on with fewer check-ins. Think: refactoring a whole module, not just one fu=
nction.</p><p>Here's what it can do inside Cursor:</p><ul><li>Search your c=
odebase by meaning, find files by name, read directory structures, and grep=
 for patterns</li><li>Suggest edits, apply them automatically, and execute =
terminal commands</li><li>A thinking variant is available for problems that=
 reward extra deliberation</li></ul><p>The tradeoff: it costs about twice a=
s much as Claude Opus 4.8, at $10 per million input tokens and $50 per mill=
ion output tokens. Use <b>Fable 5 for the hard stuff</b>, not everything.</=
p>
